            <bug_when>2009-02-17 17:13:43 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>Just to make it clear, this is NOT a configuration issue. Some SVN clients do not create or handle empty directories, and configuring them to do so is not an available option. The benefits of these SVN clients (in particular being able to use git, a far superior source code management system to SVN, locally, and merging relevant portions into SVN when ready) however, far outweigh the disadvantages of these clients, so suggestions to change SVN client won&#39;t help matters any. :-)

Derrell
</thetext>
